  "riddle": "Here is the riddle with the corrected clue:\n\n1. Seek the tournament page that hails from a picturesque region in Italy known for its stunning mountains and valleys; discover the year it was first founded; once you have that founding year, turn your attention to the 1994 edition of the clay-court Grand Slam in Paris to set a wider context.\n\n2. How high above sea level does the ground sit at the Paris venue that hosts that clay-court major — report the elevation in whole metres as your next number.\n\n3. There exists a page recounting the 1997 southern-hemisphere Grand Slam; on that subject convert a distance of 2,022 kilometres into miles and record the whole-number part of the result.\n\n4. The number whose digits you will reverse is the whole-mile tally you obtained in clue 3 — reverse its digits to produce a new numeric value for the next step.\n\n5. In the end, compute (clue 1 + clue 2 + clue 3 + clue 4) modulo 10 and give that single digit (0–9) as your final answer.",
